  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Released on 01/05/2016\u00a0UTC</p><p>This is a minor update to address bugs and add minor features.</p><p><strong>Backordered items - Automated linking</strong></p><p>When a purchase order is advanced to the &quot;Ordered&quot; status, any backordered items that can be fulfilled are linked up to the PO and advanced from &quot;backordered&quot; to &quot;ordered.&quot; When reverting a purchase order from the ordered status back to the new/draft, and then forward again to the ordered status it could link up additional backordered items\u00a0beyond the ordered qty\u00a0resulting in\u00a0more items linked to a purchase order than could be fulfilled by that purchase order. This issue has been\u00a0fixed. In addition, RepairQ will prevent reverting a purchase order\u00a0from the &quot;ordered&quot; status back to &quot;new/draft&quot; if any inventory items are already linked up to the order.</p>",
      "representation": "export_view",
